By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Senate President, Dr. Bukola Saraki, has revealed that the National Assembly’s Bill to repeal and re-enact the Companies and Allied Matters Act (CAMA) has been transmitted to President Muhammadu Buhari for his assent into law. Saraki said that once the bill is assented to by the president, it would signify Nigeria’s readiness for a modern business environment. In a series of tweets on his @BukolaSaraki handle, Saraki stated that once CAMA becomes a law, it would significantly improve the way Nigerians do business and will also tell the world that ‘Nigeria is ready for business. Saraki tweeted:  END 